WEBVTT

01:40.410 --> 01:45.950
[Speed and Love]

01:46.280 --> 01:48.740
[Episode 10]

02:08.240 --> 02:09.840
Hello, I'm Pan Kai.

02:10.009 --> 02:11.400
Everyone calls me Kai.

02:11.930 --> 02:12.930
Nice to meet you.

02:17.960 --> 02:19.620
Let's exchange contact info.

02:20.240 --> 02:21.840
Can I have your phone number?

02:24.120 --> 02:24.960
I just remembered.

02:24.960 --> 02:25.840
There are many great places to eat at

02:25.840 --> 02:26.770
near our school.

02:26.890 --> 02:28.050
I'll treat you to a meal sometime.

02:28.050 --> 02:29.120
Let's go together after class—

02:29.120 --> 02:30.240
Class is starting.

02:31.690 --> 02:32.440
Let's eat together after school.

02:32.440 --> 02:33.280
Be quiet!

02:34.120 --> 02:35.050
Class has begun.

02:36.520 --> 02:37.360
Province.

02:37.560 --> 02:38.450
Province.

02:38.610 --> 02:39.470
City.

02:39.640 --> 02:40.560
City.

02:43.340 --> 02:45.540
Class dismissed.

02:47.680 --> 02:49.610
Let's go get something delicious.

02:50.120 --> 02:50.750
Let's go.

02:55.329 --> 02:55.930
Let's go.

02:57.050 --> 02:57.900
Excuse me.

02:58.130 --> 02:59.329
Do we know each other?

03:01.130 --> 03:02.730
We can get to know each other.

03:03.010 --> 03:04.800
Hey! Hey!

03:05.640 --> 03:06.290
Hey.

03:08.840 --> 03:09.560
Hey!

03:15.080 --> 03:16.450
Who is this Pan Kai?

03:17.800 --> 03:19.890
Pan Kai? He's Thai-Chinese.

03:20.120 --> 03:22.090
He takes the college entrance exam
every year and fails every time.

03:22.090 --> 03:24.410
I heard he wants to
go to the Agricultural University,

03:24.410 --> 03:26.070
but he never managed to get in.

03:26.210 --> 03:27.340
He's also a rich kid.

03:27.610 --> 03:29.770
His family owns a car repair factory.

03:30.000 --> 03:31.890
Why is he following me around
like a puppy?

03:31.890 --> 03:33.090
I can't shake him off.

03:33.120 --> 03:35.840
Now he's even following me
to the toilet entrance.

03:35.840 --> 03:37.600
All right, enough joking around.

03:37.600 --> 03:38.860
I'm going to slip away.

04:19.490 --> 04:20.950
Did you bring everything?

04:42.090 --> 04:42.880
My bro said

04:43.650 --> 04:44.530
working for you

04:44.800 --> 04:45.760
is my honor.

04:50.730 --> 04:51.409
Take this.

04:53.880 --> 04:54.480
Okay.

04:56.480 --> 04:57.150
Jiang Mu!

04:59.050 --> 05:00.580
How could you still find me?

05:00.850 --> 05:02.090
How did you disappear

05:02.090 --> 05:03.050
while you were in the bathroom?

05:03.050 --> 05:04.980
I've been looking all over for you.

05:05.320 --> 05:06.580
None of your business.

05:06.650 --> 05:07.610
Don't you take bus 8 home?

05:07.610 --> 05:08.230
Let's go together.

05:08.230 --> 05:09.620
Don't you have a driver?

05:12.030 --> 05:13.910
I have a few questions to ask you.

05:13.930 --> 05:15.120
Let's talk on the way.

05:15.120 --> 05:17.920
-Let's go.
-You, a senior, are asking me, a newbie?

05:19.090 --> 05:20.700
You look smart.

05:21.730 --> 05:22.730
-Let's go.
-I got to go.

05:22.730 --> 05:23.650
I'm busy. Don't bother me.

05:23.650 --> 05:24.780
Where are you going?

05:27.060 --> 05:28.060
That's it for now.

05:28.200 --> 05:29.290
I'll treat you to a meal another day.

05:29.290 --> 05:30.490
When did you get back?

05:30.730 --> 05:32.130
Are you here to pick me up?

05:33.100 --> 05:33.780
Touqi—

05:35.360 --> 05:36.090
Sorry,

05:36.760 --> 05:38.690
I forgot you're not Touqi anymore.

05:39.090 --> 05:39.680
Brandy,

05:39.930 --> 05:40.860
I'm leaving now.

06:03.160 --> 06:04.960
Get in. I'll take you home.

06:15.150 --> 06:16.360
What did that guy with bleached hair

06:16.360 --> 06:18.240
give to Jin Zhao?

06:19.320 --> 06:20.720
It can't be drugs, right?

06:39.760 --> 06:41.120
What did that person just now

06:41.120 --> 06:42.320
give you?

06:42.680 --> 06:44.090
Why did he call you Touqi?

06:44.650 --> 06:46.930
You've been gone so often these days.

06:46.960 --> 06:48.360
What have you been doing?

06:52.159 --> 06:53.290
Are you done asking?

06:59.440 --> 07:00.500
Who's that person?

07:02.970 --> 07:03.760
Who?

07:04.360 --> 07:05.850
The person who stood behind you

07:05.850 --> 07:07.180
wearing white clothes.

07:08.410 --> 07:10.670
A classmate from the foundation course.

07:20.640 --> 07:21.610
Be careful.

07:57.120 --> 07:58.380
You're quite patient.

07:58.650 --> 08:00.110
Haven't seen you for days.

08:00.880 --> 08:02.080
I was just passing by.

08:02.930 --> 08:03.860
Just passing by?

08:06.750 --> 08:08.160
I came to see Lightning.

08:08.650 --> 08:09.760
You're here to see the dog

08:09.760 --> 08:11.000
but not me?

08:12.090 --> 08:14.020
Well, I'm seeing you now, aren't I?

08:18.650 --> 08:20.910
How's business at the garage these days?

08:22.930 --> 08:23.970
Not bad.

08:24.190 --> 08:25.290
Anyway, Brandy has resumed

08:25.290 --> 08:26.820
his normal business hours.

08:26.930 --> 08:28.730
But people here
tend to wake up late,

08:28.730 --> 08:29.970
so we open around 2 PM.

08:34.530 --> 08:35.799
Is he still in bed?

08:36.169 --> 08:37.370
No way.

08:38.200 --> 08:39.659
That freak barely sleeps.

08:39.679 --> 08:41.880
He gets up at six or seven every morning.

08:42.720 --> 08:43.600
That early?

08:43.890 --> 08:45.020
Where did he go then?

08:47.410 --> 08:49.290
You have so many questions—

08:50.050 --> 08:52.050
why don't you just ask him yourself?

08:52.200 --> 08:53.480
If I go ask him,

08:53.930 --> 08:55.530
I'm afraid he'll kick me out.

08:55.770 --> 08:57.290
Why would he kick you out for no reason?

08:57.290 --> 08:59.770
Because he doesn't like me.
He thinks I'm annoying.

08:59.770 --> 09:01.480
Our Jiang Mu is so adorable.

09:02.900 --> 09:05.030
Only a blind person wouldn't like you.

09:05.790 --> 09:06.890
I think so too.

09:07.030 --> 09:08.240
That'd be Brandy.

09:09.200 --> 09:11.010
What if he really kicks you out?

09:14.800 --> 09:15.890
What can I do?

09:16.250 --> 09:18.050
I'll sing for him, tell jokes,

09:18.200 --> 09:19.320
perform magic tricks,

09:19.320 --> 09:20.530
and if all else fails,

09:20.560 --> 09:21.620
I'll dance for him.

09:22.530 --> 09:23.600
You can dance?

09:23.960 --> 09:24.840
Just a little.

09:25.010 --> 09:26.870
I learned ballet when I was young.

09:26.890 --> 09:27.750
Think about it.

09:27.800 --> 09:29.560
If I actually dance for him,

09:29.760 --> 09:32.160
would he still have the heart
to kick me out?

09:35.170 --> 09:36.170
Did you hear that?

09:37.210 --> 09:39.540
Come down quickly to see your little swan.

09:44.410 --> 09:45.470
Go ahead and dance.

09:53.770 --> 09:55.630
Little swan, why are you leaving?

09:56.090 --> 09:57.290
Not dancing anymore?

10:03.440 --> 10:06.990
[Speeding Auto House]

10:50.650 --> 10:51.530
Do you think

10:51.530 --> 10:53.790
no one in this world
can keep you in check?

10:59.770 --> 11:00.770
Happy birthday,

11:01.680 --> 11:02.530
Zhao.

11:11.480 --> 11:12.410
The first wish

11:12.600 --> 11:14.440
needs to be said aloud to come true.

11:14.440 --> 11:15.770
I wish we

11:16.000 --> 11:18.800
will soon find out your real birthday.

11:27.130 --> 11:27.880
Hello everyone.

11:27.880 --> 11:29.760
I'm Jiang Mu, Jin Zhao's sister.

11:30.770 --> 11:31.650
I've decided

11:31.770 --> 11:33.570
not to call you brother anymore.

11:33.710 --> 11:36.360
I'll just call you
by your full name, Jin Zhao.

11:38.360 --> 11:39.510
I plan to stay

11:40.800 --> 11:42.260
and apply to a school here.

11:42.890 --> 11:44.050
Nana has already helped me contact

11:44.050 --> 11:45.600
a language foundation course.

11:45.600 --> 11:46.840
Do you want me to stay?

11:48.080 --> 11:50.010
I didn't expect you'd really come.

11:50.320 --> 11:51.250
Your habits,

11:51.650 --> 11:52.450
preferences,

11:52.800 --> 11:54.440
and your tone—

11:55.130 --> 11:56.620
they've long become things I remember

11:56.620 --> 11:58.280
without even having to think.

11:58.720 --> 11:59.650
I don't know why,

12:00.100 --> 12:01.050
but lately

12:01.560 --> 12:03.360
I can't help thinking about you.

12:03.410 --> 12:05.670
Not because anything special happened,

12:06.160 --> 12:08.440
I just want to make sure
you're still there.

12:08.440 --> 12:11.040
And some words have been
on the tip of my tongue—

12:11.130 --> 12:12.560
it's not that I don't want to say them,

12:12.560 --> 12:13.440
it's just that

12:13.800 --> 12:16.130
I haven't figured out
how to tell you them.

12:22.560 --> 12:23.290
Hey, handsome.

12:23.290 --> 12:25.020
Why are you here so early today?

12:25.130 --> 12:26.720
I'll call you if I want anything to eat.

12:26.720 --> 12:27.290
I'm leaving.

12:27.290 --> 12:27.770
Okay.

12:40.130 --> 12:41.680
You're quite fast today.

12:42.010 --> 12:43.720
Half an hour round trip.

12:46.130 --> 12:47.320
I know the roads and turns well now—

12:47.320 --> 12:48.920
familiar with the route now.

12:58.400 --> 12:59.090
Take this.

13:01.490 --> 13:02.730
You removed the ABS?

13:02.990 --> 13:03.990
From today on,

13:04.010 --> 13:06.880
you need to learn to control
the car completely with your feet.

13:06.880 --> 13:09.210
You can't rely on any braking assistance.

13:09.320 --> 13:10.370
If you want to go faster,

13:10.370 --> 13:11.970
you have to rely on yourself.

13:12.010 --> 13:13.170
But remember,

13:14.510 --> 13:15.840
you must remain steady.

13:17.030 --> 13:18.490
A scratch is a minor issue,

13:19.200 --> 13:21.080
but a rollover could be fatal.

13:23.410 --> 13:25.690
So do we need to change the tires too?

13:26.720 --> 13:28.010
No, just use these.

13:28.600 --> 13:31.200
It takes a good driver to drive well,
not tires.

13:40.070 --> 13:42.070
Remember, stay steady.

14:53.480 --> 14:55.340
You've been secretly drawing me,

14:55.490 --> 14:57.420
yet acting like nothing happened.

15:00.810 --> 15:02.110
If I were to ask you about it,

15:02.110 --> 15:03.910
you probably wouldn't admit it.

15:08.960 --> 15:09.650
Just wait.

15:10.210 --> 15:12.090
I'll give you a surprise too.

15:53.170 --> 15:54.770
How was your practice today?

15:56.760 --> 15:58.440
This car feels weird today.

15:58.650 --> 16:00.170
Sometimes it feels front-heavy.

16:00.170 --> 16:01.520
And sometimes the rear slides too much.

16:01.520 --> 16:02.920
It's got me all confused.

16:06.080 --> 16:07.410
Why don't you try my car?

16:14.010 --> 16:14.810
Yes, that one.

17:02.640 --> 17:03.700
What are you doing?

17:03.890 --> 17:04.650
Go on.

17:05.650 --> 17:06.760
Give me 10 minutes.

17:07.230 --> 17:09.030
Three minutes is enough for you.

17:18.050 --> 17:19.849
What did you want to see me about?

17:21.280 --> 17:22.240
I heard

17:22.650 --> 17:24.720
you came in first place
in the last race.

17:24.720 --> 17:26.530
Just tell me what you want.

17:27.329 --> 17:28.790
I've got my eye on someone.

17:30.480 --> 17:32.240
Who's the lucky one?

17:32.850 --> 17:34.180
The one who came in last.

17:34.460 --> 17:35.110
Who?

17:35.520 --> 17:36.890
In the last race.

17:37.930 --> 17:38.760
Brandy?

17:39.720 --> 17:41.720
I think his name was...

17:43.000 --> 17:43.720
Jin Zhao.

17:45.340 --> 17:46.270
Yes, that's him.

17:46.440 --> 17:47.300
Let me tell you.

17:47.310 --> 17:48.620
That guy's got skills.

17:48.930 --> 17:50.440
Control, power,

17:50.650 --> 17:51.960
and amazing adaptability too—

17:51.960 --> 17:53.890
he practically has no weaknesses.

17:55.430 --> 17:56.910
Then how did he lose to you?

18:03.650 --> 18:05.680
Wan Dayong played dirty tricks
on him last time.

18:05.680 --> 18:07.370
If he weren't mentally strong

18:07.680 --> 18:08.650
and has quick reflexes,

18:08.650 --> 18:10.280
driving backward to the finish line,

18:10.280 --> 18:11.570
he would've been eliminated.

18:11.570 --> 18:12.410
Honestly,

18:12.850 --> 18:14.510
among the top 10 drivers in the alliance,

18:14.510 --> 18:16.650
he's the only one
whose style I can't figure out.

18:16.650 --> 18:17.890
In the next race,
if nothing goes wrong

18:17.890 --> 18:19.120
with his mods...

18:19.370 --> 18:20.850
it's hard to say who'll win.

18:20.850 --> 18:21.930
At best it's 50-50.

18:24.480 --> 18:26.140
What kind of mods does he need?

18:26.170 --> 18:27.520
Reinforced seals

18:27.720 --> 18:29.380
and reinforced center shaft.

18:31.440 --> 18:33.100
These two need to be imported.

18:34.000 --> 18:34.650
Someone's trying to sabotage him

18:34.650 --> 18:36.370
so he can't rise in ranks
by accumulating points,

18:36.370 --> 18:38.900
so they bought up all the stock
in the country.

18:45.480 --> 18:47.080
Send me the product numbers.

18:47.360 --> 18:48.690
What are you going to do?

18:49.720 --> 18:50.960
Give him a push.

18:56.760 --> 18:58.040
I...

18:59.690 --> 19:00.620
Won't send them.

19:06.640 --> 19:08.000
Fine, fine.

19:08.610 --> 19:09.470
I'll send them.

19:09.910 --> 19:11.910
I'll send them to you. Just a moment.

19:15.870 --> 19:16.550
Sent.

19:18.090 --> 19:19.220
Friendly reminder,

19:19.340 --> 19:21.140
I think that guy is a bit strange.

19:21.330 --> 19:22.000
During the Scramble,

19:22.000 --> 19:24.460
he brought his girlfriend
as his navigator.

19:24.650 --> 19:26.380
They work together perfectly.

19:27.170 --> 19:28.130
She's called...

19:28.960 --> 19:30.090
Something Mu...

19:31.720 --> 19:33.040
The girl you carried away

19:33.040 --> 19:34.170
when she suddenly fainted in front of me

19:34.170 --> 19:35.500
at your birthday party.

19:38.000 --> 19:38.960
Jiang Mu.

19:41.810 --> 19:42.650
Why don't

19:42.960 --> 19:44.330
we go see her?

19:45.130 --> 19:46.850
See Jiang Mu?

19:47.890 --> 19:48.680
When?

19:49.330 --> 19:50.130
Now.

19:51.680 --> 19:52.280
Well...

19:53.100 --> 19:55.210
Can I take a shower first?

19:59.040 --> 19:59.680
How is it?

20:00.040 --> 20:01.040
My car drives well, right?

20:01.040 --> 20:02.520
Your car is automatic.

20:02.930 --> 20:04.720
That doesn't hinder drifting.

20:05.010 --> 20:06.720
The shifting efficiency and explosive power
of an auto car

20:06.720 --> 20:07.850
are far from enough.

20:07.850 --> 20:09.330
I need a manual car.

20:09.480 --> 20:11.810
Your requirements are quite advanced...

20:12.130 --> 20:14.790
But there aren't any manual cars
available now.

20:19.700 --> 20:20.790
Cousin?

20:29.380 --> 20:31.410
My cousin is the best driver
I've ever seen.

20:31.410 --> 20:32.520
I'm sure he can find something

20:32.520 --> 20:34.050
to meet your requirements.

20:39.440 --> 20:40.760
Would he be willing to teach me?

20:40.760 --> 20:42.560
Follow my lead and play it by ear.

20:45.600 --> 20:47.200
Brandy's little navigator—

20:47.330 --> 20:48.130
we meet again.

20:48.820 --> 20:50.950
My handsome and kind-hearted cousin,

20:51.000 --> 20:52.680
could you teach my little Jiang Mu

20:52.680 --> 20:54.610
a master class on drift cornering?

20:54.810 --> 20:55.680
Please.

21:00.810 --> 21:02.740
You want to learn drifting from me?

21:07.850 --> 21:08.480
Why?

21:08.720 --> 21:09.650
Don't you have

21:09.890 --> 21:11.370
better men around you?

21:17.960 --> 21:19.420
I've been in your car twice

21:19.520 --> 21:20.350
and I think

21:20.370 --> 21:22.280
you're the best drifter I know.

21:24.970 --> 21:25.650
Alright,

21:26.720 --> 21:28.180
just for that compliment,

21:28.630 --> 21:29.490
I'll teach you.

21:32.720 --> 21:34.250
But there's one condition.

21:34.520 --> 21:35.650
You have to keep it a secret

21:35.650 --> 21:37.050
and not tell anyone else.

21:37.720 --> 21:38.850
Who don't you want

21:39.520 --> 21:40.430
me to not tell?

21:42.610 --> 21:44.540
Just the few of us here should know,

21:44.850 --> 21:46.180
don't tell anyone else.

21:48.280 --> 21:49.040
Okay,

21:49.800 --> 21:50.670
sure.

21:53.960 --> 21:54.960
Give me the keys.

21:59.090 --> 22:00.600
The car I'm driving today won't work.

22:00.600 --> 22:03.000
It's too heavy, not suitable for drifting.

22:04.680 --> 22:05.740
Let's use this one.

22:07.930 --> 22:08.720
Get in.

22:10.210 --> 22:11.270
What are you doing?

22:11.450 --> 22:13.110
That's Brandy's girlfriend.

22:13.330 --> 22:15.130
Are you trying to have an affair?

22:15.310 --> 22:16.770
Using my car on top of that?

22:19.200 --> 22:20.460
Remember to record it.

22:32.720 --> 22:33.850
It's the third time

22:34.340 --> 22:36.400
you're sitting in my passenger seat,

22:37.070 --> 22:38.670
Brandy's little navigator.

22:39.070 --> 22:39.930
What about you?

22:40.280 --> 22:41.610
Do you have a navigator?

22:42.280 --> 22:42.930
No.

22:43.670 --> 22:45.190
I can't trust anyone.

22:49.170 --> 22:50.570
What do you want to learn?

22:51.040 --> 22:52.570
I've watched many drift races,

22:52.570 --> 22:54.160
especially exhibition matches

22:54.160 --> 22:55.610
where drivers have complete control

22:55.610 --> 22:56.810
over their cars.

22:57.550 --> 22:58.410
They can draw various shapes

22:58.410 --> 22:59.850
with their tire marks.

23:00.570 --> 23:02.170
I just can't control it well.

23:04.210 --> 23:05.650
What shape do you want?

23:11.440 --> 23:12.440
The number three.

23:13.330 --> 23:14.730
It's a horizontal three—

23:14.890 --> 23:15.950
two semi-circles.

23:18.520 --> 23:20.150
Drifting isn't difficult, but

23:20.150 --> 23:21.360
I'm curious

23:21.500 --> 23:23.760
what these two semi-circles represent.

23:25.240 --> 23:26.780
You're gesturing it correctly.

23:26.780 --> 23:28.020
Just add

23:28.040 --> 23:29.030
two little tails at the end

23:29.030 --> 23:31.630
and it would be better
if they can be connected.

23:34.240 --> 23:35.300
Do you understand?

23:35.960 --> 23:37.620
That's truly a perfect shape.

23:40.680 --> 23:41.290
Alright,

23:42.040 --> 23:43.170
I'll teach you this.

23:55.200 --> 23:56.160
What's this for?

23:56.760 --> 23:57.560
Wrap it where?

23:58.470 --> 23:59.800
No food delivery today.

24:00.780 --> 24:03.580
Go tie your right hand
to the steering wheel.

24:04.870 --> 24:07.180
Control your steering angle.

24:07.410 --> 24:09.590
The smaller the angle,
the faster you return the wheel,

24:09.590 --> 24:11.250
and the faster you take turns.

24:11.560 --> 24:13.800
Let your brain develop muscle memory.

24:17.420 --> 24:18.820
How long do I keep it tied?

24:21.170 --> 24:23.890
Until you can handle it effortlessly.

24:40.880 --> 24:43.110
♪ Make it fast, never slow down ♪

24:43.130 --> 24:45.610
♪ Show my transcendent stance ♪

24:45.630 --> 24:46.750
♪ Speeding love ♪

24:46.770 --> 24:48.170
♪ Whether I succeed or fail ♪

24:48.200 --> 24:50.340
♪ I just want to be free ♪

24:50.370 --> 24:52.930
♪ Shining star, heart on fire ♪

24:52.950 --> 24:55.200
♪ The odds of winning are 100% ♪

24:55.230 --> 24:58.050
♪ Make my name be known
throughout the world ♪

24:58.070 --> 25:00.150
♪ You just wait and see ♪

25:00.630 --> 25:01.660
♪ Start my engine ♪

25:01.680 --> 25:03.240
♪ The exhaust pipe will start roaring ♪

25:03.260 --> 25:04.110
♪ Never slowing down ♪

25:04.150 --> 25:05.630
♪ We go higher and higher ♪

25:05.760 --> 25:08.000
♪ I can't wait to enjoy
this minute of passion ♪

25:08.020 --> 25:09.720
♪ Thrilling love,
my heart is beating fast ♪

25:09.820 --> 25:12.050
♪ Make it fast, never slow down ♪

25:12.090 --> 25:14.560
♪ Show my transcendent stance ♪

25:14.590 --> 25:15.710
♪ Speeding love ♪

25:15.730 --> 25:17.130
♪ Whether I succeed or fail ♪

25:17.150 --> 25:19.240
♪ I just want to be free ♪

25:19.290 --> 25:21.850
♪ Shining star, heart on fire ♪

25:21.870 --> 25:24.120
♪ The odds of winning are 100% ♪

25:24.150 --> 25:26.970
♪ Make my name be known
throughout the world ♪

25:26.990 --> 25:29.070
♪ You just wait and see ♪

25:29.890 --> 25:32.270
♪ Make it fast, never slow down ♪

25:32.290 --> 25:34.340
♪ Show my transcendent stance ♪

25:34.370 --> 25:35.770
♪ Speeding love ♪

25:35.790 --> 25:37.020
♪ Whether I succeed or fail ♪

25:37.040 --> 25:39.220
♪ I just want to be free ♪

25:39.240 --> 25:41.810
♪ Shining star, heart on fire ♪

25:41.830 --> 25:44.140
♪ The odds of winning are 100% ♪

25:42.850 --> 25:43.810
He's serious.

25:44.160 --> 25:46.630
♪ Make my name be known
throughout the world ♪

25:46.650 --> 25:48.990
♪ You just wait and see ♪

25:51.200 --> 25:52.680
Look at the tire marks on the ground.

25:52.680 --> 25:53.610
Circles and the figure 8—

25:53.610 --> 25:55.140
you've just learned those.

25:55.530 --> 25:56.800
To change the shape,

25:57.090 --> 25:59.600
you need both route design and technique.

25:59.850 --> 26:02.000
You need speed to drift.

26:02.140 --> 26:04.150
So before every drift,

26:04.170 --> 26:06.030
you must drive in a straight line.

26:20.150 --> 26:21.410
The first semicircle.

26:29.890 --> 26:31.420
The little tail you wanted.

26:33.580 --> 26:34.830
That's interesting.

26:50.780 --> 26:52.110
The second semicircle.

26:53.370 --> 26:54.430
Do you understand?

26:56.650 --> 26:57.280
I got it.

26:57.610 --> 26:58.740
The path is perfect.

27:01.810 --> 27:03.840
That's exactly the pattern I wanted.

27:03.840 --> 27:04.630
Let me try.

27:20.560 --> 27:21.760
Place your hand here.

27:25.760 --> 27:26.960
Relax this part a bit.

27:28.280 --> 27:29.740
Relax your shoulders too.

27:31.240 --> 27:32.040
Grip it here.

27:33.720 --> 27:34.790
What are you guys

27:34.810 --> 27:36.130
really up to?

27:37.000 --> 27:38.480
It's a secret.

27:38.930 --> 27:41.130
Look at you being all tight-lipped now.

27:41.360 --> 27:42.630
You can go ask Lin Sui.

27:50.130 --> 27:50.810
Okay.

27:51.240 --> 27:52.370
Relax your

27:53.130 --> 27:54.090
shoulders.

27:55.180 --> 27:55.870
Alright.

28:09.370 --> 28:11.500
Why don't you pause when shifting gears?

28:11.500 --> 28:14.090
One, you're not releasing the clutch
decisively enough.

28:14.090 --> 28:16.350
Your acceleration isn't smooth enough.

28:17.520 --> 28:20.800
I forgot how to say it in Chinese...

28:22.170 --> 28:22.890
May I?

28:32.880 --> 28:33.740
Just like this.

28:33.760 --> 28:34.570
Push it down

28:34.850 --> 28:35.650
in an instant.

29:28.410 --> 29:29.370
Did you see that?

29:29.520 --> 29:30.440
I did it!

29:31.480 --> 29:32.520
You surprised me.

29:34.170 --> 29:35.440
I like Chinese girls.

29:39.900 --> 29:41.980
I also like handsome boys too.

29:45.520 --> 29:46.760
Practice well.

29:48.880 --> 29:50.480
I hope your dreams come true.

29:51.340 --> 29:52.100
Thank you.

29:56.980 --> 29:59.220
You're amazing, Mu.

30:04.490 --> 30:05.620
Thanks for your car.

30:06.760 --> 30:08.020
Quite impressive, young girl.

30:08.020 --> 30:11.680
You've got both the car
and the people wrapped around your finger.

30:14.170 --> 30:15.230
We'll be going now.

30:16.400 --> 30:17.200
Thank you.

30:23.510 --> 30:25.270
My cousin seems

30:25.960 --> 30:27.290
to be interested in you.

30:28.710 --> 30:30.530
He's just pretending to pursue me.

30:30.530 --> 30:31.290
What?

30:40.110 --> 30:42.260
Hand on gear, feet on gas and clutch,

30:42.280 --> 30:44.010
your movements have to be fast.

30:44.280 --> 30:45.370
For sharp turns,

30:45.520 --> 30:47.280
turn the wheel and pull the handbrake—

30:47.280 --> 30:48.040
spin back.

30:53.950 --> 30:55.280
Straight-line acceleration
depends on the mods.

30:55.280 --> 30:57.040
Just be quick with your hands and feet.

30:57.040 --> 30:59.770
Taking corners fast
is what makes you truly fast.

31:07.680 --> 31:10.200
When taking corners, go with the momentum.

31:11.130 --> 31:12.200
Your rear end loses control

31:12.200 --> 31:14.240
because you're too slow at every step,

31:14.240 --> 31:15.570
especially braking.

31:16.000 --> 31:18.240
If you brake too slowly,
inertia will control you.

31:18.240 --> 31:19.970
Don't let inertia control you.

31:20.110 --> 31:21.840
You need to make use of inertia.

31:30.890 --> 31:32.280
It's just like stir-frying.

31:32.280 --> 31:33.740
Whether a dish tastes good

31:34.170 --> 31:35.820
depends on heat, seasoning,

31:36.130 --> 31:37.200
and ingredients.

31:39.050 --> 31:39.960
As for grip,

31:40.680 --> 31:42.740
it's divided between acceleration,

31:43.000 --> 31:43.810
braking,

31:45.240 --> 31:47.570
and steering—three ways to split the pie.

31:51.440 --> 31:52.440
When driving straight,

31:52.440 --> 31:54.810
100% of grip is
used for deceleration.

31:55.330 --> 31:56.330
When cornering,

31:56.890 --> 31:58.620
steering takes away some grip.

31:59.720 --> 32:02.050
If the heat is too high,
the food will burn.

32:02.090 --> 32:04.370
Release the gas, stop accelerating.

32:04.680 --> 32:06.200
Only when you simmer in low heat

32:06.200 --> 32:07.520
can flavors develop.

32:14.810 --> 32:17.410
The front wheels
gain more load due to inertia.

32:18.010 --> 32:19.330
Delay your braking point,

32:19.330 --> 32:21.720
and the whole grip pie gets bigger.

32:43.330 --> 32:45.350
Step on the gas pedal
immediately after the turn

32:45.350 --> 32:46.700
to exit the turn faster.

32:52.870 --> 32:54.240
What if the car body is unstable

32:54.240 --> 32:56.570
when going through consecutive S-turns?

32:57.330 --> 32:58.240
With beef,

32:58.530 --> 33:01.000
you can't stir-fry too long
or it gets tough.

33:01.410 --> 33:02.170
Similarly,

33:03.040 --> 33:05.240
gentle S-curves are high-speed turns—

33:05.310 --> 33:06.590
you need to be fast.

33:08.040 --> 33:09.090
So,

33:09.940 --> 33:11.420
brake as late as possible,

33:12.670 --> 33:13.800
or don't brake at all

33:14.210 --> 33:15.300
to maintain speed.

33:15.820 --> 33:16.730
That's right.

33:19.300 --> 33:21.170
Quick stir-fry needs high heat.

33:22.040 --> 33:24.930
High heat quickly seals in the moisture

33:24.960 --> 33:26.160
keeping food tender.

33:28.050 --> 33:29.160
For S-curves,

33:31.850 --> 33:33.250
stick to the inside line.

33:33.850 --> 33:35.660
Treat the S-curve as

33:35.680 --> 33:37.960
one straight line for the fastest path.

33:48.890 --> 33:49.650
Try it.

34:48.790 --> 34:51.159
Why does this car feel
so easy to drive today?

34:51.159 --> 34:52.000
Obviously,

34:52.520 --> 34:54.370
you were running with sandbags before.

34:54.370 --> 34:56.639
Without them, of course you'll fly.

34:58.140 --> 34:58.820
Thanks.

34:59.290 --> 35:00.290
Don't mention it.

35:00.930 --> 35:02.140
There are 20 deliveries later.

35:02.140 --> 35:04.430
Once you're done showing off,
get back to work.

35:04.430 --> 35:05.940
I'll finish within 30 minutes.

35:05.940 --> 35:08.060
30 minutes is your limit?

35:11.410 --> 35:12.330
15 minutes.

35:12.850 --> 35:13.960
That's ambitious.

35:14.210 --> 35:15.850
That's worthy of my car

35:16.010 --> 35:17.270
and my cooking skills.

35:24.930 --> 35:26.130
Don't drink too much.

35:28.240 --> 35:29.170
Do you remember?

35:29.930 --> 35:31.480
The customer who speaks Chinese

35:31.480 --> 35:33.610
at the restaurant,
the rich young man.

35:34.640 --> 35:36.790
He definitely
didn't just come for the food.

35:36.790 --> 35:37.940
-It seems—
-I know.

35:39.120 --> 35:40.120
You know?

35:40.290 --> 35:42.120
You don't even use your brain!

35:42.250 --> 35:43.310
You think you know?

35:43.480 --> 35:44.000
Let me tell you.

35:44.000 --> 35:47.600
Isn't he just that guy who puked
after eating too many dumplings?

35:50.120 --> 35:51.330
How did you know?

35:53.160 --> 35:54.480
The car he drives

35:54.850 --> 35:56.330
and that vibe he gives off—

35:56.890 --> 35:58.440
he's here for Jin Zhao.

36:02.680 --> 36:04.240
So what vibe did you pick up?

36:04.730 --> 36:06.600
The smell of male rivalry.

36:09.730 --> 36:11.250
Should we talk to Zhao about it?

36:11.250 --> 36:12.210
No need.

36:15.440 --> 36:15.890
But...

36:15.910 --> 36:16.740
Enough.

36:17.480 --> 36:18.600
Look at you,

36:18.810 --> 36:19.960
not acting like a father at all,

36:19.960 --> 36:21.490
just drinking all the time.

36:21.960 --> 36:24.020
We really don't need to talk about it?

36:25.250 --> 36:26.250
I'm not drinking.

36:45.690 --> 36:46.480
Excuse me,

36:46.730 --> 36:48.410
could you tell me how to get to EA class?

36:48.410 --> 36:50.510
I'm sorry,
I can't understand what you're saying.

36:50.510 --> 36:51.180
Thank you.

37:00.970 --> 37:03.140
Mr. Chen is so annoying,

37:03.160 --> 37:05.420
always pushing me to submit my homework.

37:05.440 --> 37:07.210
Then you should get it done faster.

37:07.210 --> 37:08.610
Oh my god, Jiang Mu, look!

37:09.440 --> 37:10.730
He's so handsome!

37:11.370 --> 37:12.830
Is he a parent or a student?

37:15.150 --> 37:16.030
He's my parent.

37:18.470 --> 37:20.070
Is that your genius brother?

37:20.480 --> 37:21.730
Can I meet him?

37:24.160 --> 37:24.890
Did you hear that?

37:24.890 --> 37:26.550
Mr. Chen is calling you again.

37:27.080 --> 37:28.120
Go quickly!

37:28.660 --> 37:29.730
I heard it.

37:57.470 --> 37:58.730
Why are you here early?

38:00.930 --> 38:03.130
I came to see how you're doing in school.

38:04.160 --> 38:06.090
I'm doing excellently, of course.

38:10.690 --> 38:12.690
My classmate just said

38:12.930 --> 38:14.860
she thought you were a student too.

38:16.890 --> 38:18.080
I do look young.

38:21.680 --> 38:22.950
How shameless.

38:30.200 --> 38:31.240
Hello everyone.

38:36.160 --> 38:37.290
Respected parents,

38:37.520 --> 38:39.850
thank you all for coming

38:40.440 --> 38:43.160
to today's open day event.

38:43.730 --> 38:46.480
Although we are
just a language training school,

38:47.080 --> 38:48.510
we still pay great attention

38:48.510 --> 38:50.120
to students' overall development

38:50.120 --> 38:52.380
and offer various interesting courses.

38:52.380 --> 38:55.500
We come from different places.

38:56.480 --> 38:57.160
Mu.

38:59.320 --> 39:01.640
Mu, please come up and say a few words.

39:12.120 --> 39:14.250
Hello everyone, I'm Jiang Mu.

39:14.690 --> 39:17.020
I enjoy my time studying here

39:17.040 --> 39:19.400
and am glad to meet everyone here.

39:19.480 --> 39:22.330
Although we've only spent a short

39:22.520 --> 39:24.080
time together,

39:24.400 --> 39:26.800
I really like the learning atmosphere here

39:26.800 --> 39:29.360
and I'm happy to be friends with you all.

39:29.540 --> 39:31.270
I hope in the days to come

39:31.290 --> 39:33.600
we can all get along well.

39:33.980 --> 39:36.000
I'll continue working hard on my English

39:36.000 --> 39:37.520
and the local language.

39:37.850 --> 39:41.120
I hope to integrate more
with everyone in the future.

40:14.930 --> 40:15.690
Are you cold?

40:28.020 --> 40:30.020
Why did it suddenly rain so heavily?

40:30.080 --> 40:31.540
This is how it's like here.

40:32.040 --> 40:34.290
It's just a passing shower.
It'll be gone in no time.

40:34.290 --> 40:35.250
Let's wait a bit.

41:00.260 --> 41:06.650
♪ Perhaps the weather's damp and mild ♪

41:00.440 --> 41:01.440
To warm my hand.

41:06.670 --> 41:10.510
♪ Perhaps it's about the habit
of bearing ♪

41:11.220 --> 41:14.500
♪ A certain bitter emotion ♪

41:14.520 --> 41:20.590
♪ For you, it's all too easy ♪

41:21.540 --> 41:27.250
♪ To be happy or heartbroken,
as transparent as I can be ♪

41:28.530 --> 41:34.390
♪ Crossing the line for love,
I've walked 10,000 kilometers ♪

41:35.490 --> 41:41.650
♪ Brave enough to be sure is my instinct ♪

41:41.810 --> 41:42.960
♪ I believe ♪

41:42.990 --> 41:47.160
♪ Maybe it just takes a little resolve ♪

41:47.410 --> 41:50.640
♪ To turn wishes into shooting stars ♪

41:51.220 --> 41:56.250
♪ Mirroring the eyes that gaze at me ♪

42:01.850 --> 42:09.470
♪ Crossing the orbit,
stepping into your life ♪
